    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>I went ahead and checked my dependency tree, and sure enough there was a conflicting <code>java.xml</code> module in there!</p>\n<pre><code>            &lt;exclusions&gt;\n                &lt;exclusion&gt;\n                    &lt;groupId&gt;xerces&lt;/groupId&gt;\n                    &lt;artifactId&gt;xercesImpl&lt;/artifactId&gt;\n                &lt;/exclusion&gt;\n                &lt;exclusion&gt;\n                    &lt;groupId&gt;xml-apis&lt;/groupId&gt;\n                    &lt;artifactId&gt;xml-apis&lt;/artifactId&gt;\n                &lt;/exclusion&gt;\n            &lt;/exclusions&gt;\n</code></pre>\n<p>I found the 2 offenders that added that (in my test scope), added those exclusions, working now.</p>\n<p>Why does Intellij and VS Code code editors not complain about these lines, not sure.</p>\n"
  } ],
