  "title" : "Eclipse - error &quot;org.w3c.dom is accessible from more than one module&quot; when doing import",
  "body" : "<p>I have an issue in Eclipse that does not reproduce with VS Code or Intellij.</p>\n<p>When I import a certain package I get this error:\n<code>The package org.w3c.dom is accessible from more than one module: &lt;unnamed&gt;, java.xml</code></p>\n<p>This project works from VS Code, Intellij and builds from from CLI. But Eclipse struggles on this.</p>\n<p>I hesitate to make any dep tree changes because Intellij and VS Code seem to not have this issue.</p>\n<p>Is there some reason why Eclipse is having this issue that someone can trigger me to understand?</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://i.sstatic.net/M6TXDIrp.png\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\"><img src=\"https://i.sstatic.net/M6TXDIrp.png\" alt=\"Eclipse issue with accessible from more than one module\" /></a></p>\n"
